<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Nobdy" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Nobódy</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Nóbody,</orth> (mostly in two words, sometimes hyphened in O. Edd.) no person, no one: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.165" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 165</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.645" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 645</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.129" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.73" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.246" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 246</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 4, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 5, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.269" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.210" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 210</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.52" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.124" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 59</bibl>. <cit><quote>played by the picture of N.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 136</bibl></cit> (allusion to a print prefixed to the comedy of <emph>No-body and Some-body,</emph> or to an engraving on the old ballad of <emph>The Well-spoken Nobody</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>